Step 1: In a small heavy-bottomed saucepan, place carrots, orange juice, margarine and sugar. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer gently on low heat, stirring occasionally for 15 minutes or until the carrots are tender-crisp. Step 2: Remove from heat and toss with chopped fresh mint. Nutritional Facts Calories (Kcals): 80 % Daily Value Total Fat: 2g Saturated fat: 0g Trans Fat: 0g Polyunsaturates: 0.5g Omega-6: 0.5g Omega-3: 0g Monounsaturates: 1g 3% 0% Cholesterol:0mg 0% Sodium:95mg 4% Potassium: 410mg 9% Total Carbohydrate: 14g Dietary Fibre: 3g Sugars: 7g 8% 12% Protein: 1g Vitamin A: 380% Vitamin C: 30% Calcium: 4% Iron: 2% Preparation Time: 5 minutes Cook Time: 15 minutes Total Time: 20 minutes http://www.becel.ca/en/becel/HeartHealthyRecipes/Side-Dishes/Orange-Glazed-Carrots.aspx